data.title: Mahesh Bhupathi: Movies, Photos, Videos, News, Biography & Birthday
data.meta_description: mahesh bhupathi: Check out the list of all mahesh bhupathi movies along with photos, videos, biography and birthday. Also find latest mahesh bhupathi news on Times of India.
data.text:
I definitely need a partner who's more athletic, more agile: Bopanna on playing with Balaji in Olympics

TIMESOFINDIA.COM / Jul 16, 2024, 12:35 (IST)

Rohan Bopanna, preparing for his last Olympics with N Sriram Balaji, saw success at the French Open, Houston ATP 250, and Davis Cup. Chosen over Yuki Bhambri for agility, they'll train at the Hamburg Open. Despite the experience gap, Bopanna aims for a medal with strong support in Paris.

Rohan Bopanna to pair with either Balaji or Yuki Bhambri at Paris Games

TIMESOFINDIA.COM / May 20, 2024, 17:20 (IST)

India's top doubles player, Rohan Bopanna, will choose either N Sriram Balaji or Yuki Bhambri as his partner for the Paris Olympics, with the All India Tennis Association (AITA) likely to approve his selection. The combinations will be discussed by the selection committee. Ranked fourth in the world, the 44-year-old Bopanna, being a top-10 player, is entitled to select his partner according to the rules.

'BCCI needs to enforce Sale of RCB,' says Indian tennis great after franchise's torrid run this IPL

TIMESOFINDIA.COM / Apr 16, 2024, 11:03 (IST)

With the weakest bowling attack among all the 10 franchises, and their spearhead Mohammed Siraj sitting out of the game against SRH, RCB's bowling was thoroughly exposed against Sunrisers Hyderabad and it all came circling back to the owners, who didn't pick the team wisely during the December auction last year. RCB on Monday suffered their fifth straight defeat and sixth in 7 matches.

Lara Dutta, mahesh bhupathi, and daughter Saira pose for a perfect family picture on the occasion of the couple’s 13th anniversary

etimes.in / Feb 20, 2024, 07:13 (IST)

Lara Dutta and mahesh bhupathi celebrate their 13th wedding anniversary on Instagram with their daughter, Saira. Fans admire their enduring love that evolved from a friendship during ‘Koffee with Karan’ and Lara's shoot for ‘Housefull’. They continue to cherish their journey together.

From tennis court to horse racing, Piperno relishes strengthening RCTC

TNN / Feb 29, 2024, 19:41 (IST)

He may have made a flawless transition from tennis court to racetrack, but there is no dearth of challenges for Enrico Piperno. The 62-year-old now faces an acid test as the chairman of racing operations at the Royal Calcutta Turf Club (RCTC) which is set to host the biggest weekend of Indian racing, the 62nd edition of the Invitation Weekend on March 2 and 3.

Bopanna, Ebden hit it off as a pair

TNN / Jan 29, 2024, 09:45 (IST)

Rohan Bopanna, playing his 61st Grand Slam doubles event with his 19th partner, found success with his consistent partner Matt Ebden at Melbourne Park. Despite early exits in the first two majors, the duo showed their potential by claiming a Masters 1000 title. Their recent triumph in Melbourne has changed the perception of Bopanna as the 'forever groomsman'.

Rohan Bopanna set to make tennis history as oldest world No. 1 in men's doubles

TIMESOFINDIA.COM / Jan 24, 2024, 09:57 (IST)

Rohan Bopanna, India's seasoned tennis player, is set to become the oldest player to achieve World No. 1 ranking in men's doubles. Bopanna, partnering with Australian Matthew Ebden, qualified for Australian Open semifinals after defeating sixth-seeded Argentinian duo Máximo González and Andrés Molteni. Bopanna and Ebden will face unseeded Tomas Machac and Zhizhen Zhang in the semis.

How Sumit Nagal overcame fund crunch, injury and Covid

TNN / Jan 17, 2024, 08:43 (IST)

Sumit Nagal returned to the big stage in grand style, pulling off one of the biggest victories of his career by stunning world number 27 Alexander Bublik of Kazakhstan in straight sets to breeze into the Australian Open second round on Tuesday. The 26-year-old will next play China's Juncheng Shang, ranked 140, on Thursday. If he happens to win the second round, there is potential third round clash with world No. 2 Carlos Alcaraz of Spain.

Kaun Banega Crorepati 15: Class 7th student Sonakshi's dad complains about her overeating and burps; Host Amitabh Bachchan gives a hilarious reaction

etimes.in / Dec 01, 2023, 07:10 (IST)

Sonakshi uses first lifeline for Rs 3000. 'Audience Poll' lifeline reveals mahesh bhupathi hasn't represented India in badminton. Amitabh Bachchan reads Sonakshi's report card, mentioning her likes and dislikes. Sonakshi's parents share her love for food and her habit of burping. Sonakshi confidently selects 'Biosphere' for the part of the world where life exists. She uses 'Ask the Expert' lifeline to guess 'Rugby' as the sport named after an English school. Sonakshi wins Rs 80,000 in Super Sandook and revives 'Ask the Expert'. She guesses 'France' as the country with the most time zones. Sonakshi flips the question on the first Indian-American to win Scripps National Spelling Bee. She quits the game without knowing the northernmost island of Andaman and Nicobar Islands, which is Landfall Island.

The love of playing Davis Cup is missing, now it's like just another tournament for players: Rohan Bopanna

PTI / Sep 15, 2023, 12:58 (IST)

Indian tennis player Rohan Bopanna has expressed his disappointment with the current state of the Davis Cup, stating that the passion for playing the tournament is diminishing among the current generation of players. Bopanna believes that the team camaraderie and unity that used to be present in the Davis Cup has been lost in recent years, and he hopes to bring it back for a successful team.
